WEBVTT

00:00.533 --> 00:03.469
♪

00:03.471 --> 00:05.104
Oh, Princess Twilight,

00:05.106 --> 00:07.339
everypony at the
hospital is so excited

00:07.341 --> 00:12.311
I'm never too busy to visit
sick foals! I can't believe

00:12.313 --> 00:15.481
a whole class just came
down with the Horsey Hives.

00:15.483 --> 00:17.750
... on school
picture day, too!

00:20.453 --> 00:24.356
Oh! The poor dears really
do need cheering up.

00:24.358 --> 00:28.627
We'll bring snacks; I'll read
to them and get them gifts.

00:28.629 --> 00:30.295
Food and presents
always cheer me up!

00:35.035 --> 00:36.135
We'll see you soon.

00:38.505 --> 00:41.440
OK, if we want to be at
the hospital by lunch,

00:41.442 --> 00:43.542
then we have three hours
to buy get-well presents,

00:43.544 --> 00:45.444
borrow a book from
the schoolhouse

00:45.446 --> 00:48.080
and pick up treats.

00:48.082 --> 00:50.249
It's a lot, but if we
stick to the schedule,

00:50.251 --> 00:52.084
I know we can get
it all done.

00:52.086 --> 00:53.719
Yeah, knock on wood!

00:53.721 --> 00:55.154
[knock at door]

00:57.590 --> 00:59.324
Surprise!

00:59.326 --> 01:00.592
[baby giggle]

01:00.594 --> 01:02.694
Oh, my gosh!

01:04.764 --> 01:07.366
How's my
favorite niece?

01:07.368 --> 01:10.836
[high voice] I'm good! I was
hoping my favorite aunt

01:10.838 --> 01:13.272
could watch me for
a few hours!

01:13.274 --> 01:15.374
I hope you're
not too busy!

01:15.376 --> 01:17.476
Actually, we kind of are--

01:17.478 --> 01:20.679
Busy? Psh! Would the Best
Aunt Ever be "too busy"

01:20.681 --> 01:23.215
to spend time with this
adorable little one?

01:25.718 --> 01:26.785
No!

01:29.856 --> 01:33.392
<i>♪ My little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

01:33.394 --> 01:35.360
<i>♪ Aaaahhh</i>

01:35.362 --> 01:39.798
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be. ♪</i>

01:39.800 --> 01:44.303
<i>♪ Until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me. ♪</i>

01:44.305 --> 01:49.575
<i>♪ Sharing kindness</i>
<i>♪ it's an easy feat</i>

01:49.577 --> 01:52.678
<i>♪ And magic makes it</i>
<i>all complete! ♪</i>

01:52.680 --> 01:54.780
<i>♪ To have my little pony</i>

01:54.782 --> 01:58.283
<i>♪ Do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

01:58.285 --> 01:59.351
♪

02:05.158 --> 02:06.558
[kissing sounds]

02:06.560 --> 02:07.693
[giggles]

02:10.763 --> 02:13.832
Flur-ry, I've got
a surprise for you!

02:21.374 --> 02:24.376
Just a couple of toys that
reminded me of Flurry!

02:24.378 --> 02:26.545
[clatter]

02:26.547 --> 02:29.281
[Flurry gurgles with excitement]

02:30.551 --> 02:34.586
I've done some shopping
for Flurry Heart!

02:34.588 --> 02:38.757
You're so sweet. You
didn't have to do all that!

02:38.759 --> 02:40.859
I know, but I
can't help myself!

02:40.861 --> 02:42.928
Best! Aunt! Ever!

02:44.430 --> 02:45.898
Open this one, Flurry!

02:45.900 --> 02:51.270
[baby talk]

02:51.272 --> 02:52.271
[growl]

02:52.273 --> 02:54.339
[laugh]

02:54.341 --> 02:58.544
Exactly! They're bears!
You're one smart cookie!

02:58.546 --> 03:04.883
♪

03:04.885 --> 03:07.386
[excited chatter]

03:07.388 --> 03:10.522
♪

03:27.807 --> 03:30.576
We'll just put Flurry's
things over here, Twiley!

03:30.578 --> 03:32.277
Uh huh, totally!

03:33.846 --> 03:35.847
Mashed peas:
her favorite.

03:35.849 --> 03:41.887
And diapers, extra diapers,
oh and backup extra diapers.

03:41.889 --> 03:45.591
Mashed peas: her favorite.
Wait. Did I say that already?

03:47.327 --> 03:48.760
Uh-huh.

03:48.762 --> 03:53.732
Oh! And this is the most
important thing of all!

03:53.734 --> 03:55.834
Her "whammy".

03:55.836 --> 03:57.803
I take it Flurry named it?

03:57.805 --> 04:00.772
Yup. If she gets fussy,
just give her the whammy

04:00.774 --> 04:02.774
and she'll calm
right down.

04:02.776 --> 04:04.710
You getting all
this, Twiley?

04:04.712 --> 04:06.245
Whammy! Got it!

04:07.548 --> 04:11.850
You remember my friend from
the royal guard, Spearhead?

04:14.387 --> 04:17.923
Honestly, all of your friends'
names are very similar.

04:17.925 --> 04:21.260
Well, he has a pop-up art
show at the Ponyville Cafe

04:21.262 --> 04:23.362
and we decided to go
at the last minute.

04:23.364 --> 04:25.297
We're not exactly
art enthusiasts

04:25.299 --> 04:27.699
but we could really
use a night out.

04:27.701 --> 04:30.902
That's what I said.
Isn't that what I said?

04:33.006 --> 04:35.674
Either way, are you
sure you can watch her?

04:37.343 --> 04:38.677
Uh uh uh!

04:40.913 --> 04:46.285
Have no fear! The Best-Aunt-Ever
has everything under control!

04:46.287 --> 04:48.287
♪

04:48.289 --> 04:49.955
[kiss]

04:49.957 --> 04:51.723
Thanks again, Twiley!

04:53.426 --> 04:55.494
OK, let's grab that
wharmmy thing and go!

04:59.999 --> 05:03.602
Ooh, you wanna pretend
we're the bears?

05:03.604 --> 05:05.671
I suppose we have
time for a quick game.

05:07.807 --> 05:08.907
Do we though?

05:08.909 --> 05:10.409
Hey!

05:10.411 --> 05:13.779
All right, rawr!
I'm gonna getcha!

05:13.781 --> 05:14.780
[squeak]

05:14.782 --> 05:15.981
Agh!

05:15.983 --> 05:18.383
[sigh]

05:18.385 --> 05:21.386
You should catch her soon
cause we've got lots to do!

05:21.388 --> 05:24.589
Horsey-hive covered foals
counting on us, remember?

05:24.591 --> 05:28.960
Got it. Rawr, rawr!
I'm catching up! Rawr!

05:36.602 --> 05:38.036
RAWWWWWR!

05:38.038 --> 05:39.404
[squeal]

05:41.407 --> 05:44.443
Uh oh. Sorry, bug.
Did that scare you?

05:44.445 --> 05:45.911
[knock knock]

05:45.913 --> 05:48.613
It's OK! It's just
Auntie Twiley!

05:55.822 --> 05:57.723
You know, that was a
very advanced spell

05:57.725 --> 05:59.691
for somepony your age.

05:59.693 --> 06:02.594
Looks like you're already taking
after your Auntie Twiley!

06:07.367 --> 06:11.069
All right, that was pretty
adorable. But now--

06:11.071 --> 06:12.804
I know, Spike. We're leaving.

06:12.806 --> 06:16.074
[stomach growls]

06:16.076 --> 06:17.776
I just have to feed
her real quick.

06:38.831 --> 06:43.435
Is this art...
or a mistake?

06:43.437 --> 06:45.103
I have no idea.

06:45.105 --> 06:48.106
But who cares? We're
not changing diapers.

06:48.108 --> 06:52.043
Shining Armor! Cadance!
How are the new 'rents?!

06:52.045 --> 06:53.111
Give me some hoof!

06:56.115 --> 07:02.087
It is so! Good! To see you
dudes! Thanks for coming!

07:02.089 --> 07:04.689
Of course! We're
having a great time!

07:04.691 --> 07:06.625
Loving all the art!

07:07.960 --> 07:09.694
Uh, that's a trash can.

07:13.666 --> 07:16.668
So it is. I knew that!

07:16.670 --> 07:18.603
But hey, who's to
say it's not art?

07:18.605 --> 07:20.038
Art can be anything
that speaks to you.

07:20.040 --> 07:21.540
It changed my world.

07:23.176 --> 07:29.080
This is my latest piece: A
Thousand Nights in a Hallway.

07:29.082 --> 07:33.852
Wow, I guess nighttime in a
hallway can be pretty dark.

07:33.854 --> 07:35.821
There is none more dark.

07:35.823 --> 07:37.556
Yeah. Totally.

07:39.459 --> 07:41.159
We're just so happy to be here!

07:41.161 --> 07:44.629
Usually we're covered
in mashed peas by now.

07:44.631 --> 07:46.731
When they said mashed
peas were her favorite--

07:46.733 --> 07:47.999
[splat]

07:48.001 --> 07:50.669
[giggle]

07:50.671 --> 07:53.538
--did they mean her favorite
thing to decorate a room with?

07:53.540 --> 07:58.910
[giggle]

07:58.912 --> 08:01.847
Aw, come on, Spike.
That wasn't too bad!

08:01.849 --> 08:05.584
Yeah and we're only twenty
minutes behind schedule.

08:05.586 --> 08:11.256
Twenty minutes? It's fine.
We can totally do this.

08:11.258 --> 08:12.958
[splat]

08:12.960 --> 08:14.025
[weak laugh]

08:19.732 --> 08:23.001
OK, we just need to grab some
toys and we are out of here!

08:26.606 --> 08:28.573
Rawrr!

08:33.546 --> 08:35.981
Well, I know a game
that's even more fun...

08:35.983 --> 08:37.649
and more efficient.

08:37.651 --> 08:39.818
Playing race cart! Ha ha!

08:39.820 --> 08:44.656
[excited shouts]

08:44.658 --> 08:45.757
Woohoo!

08:45.759 --> 08:48.593
[baby giggles]

08:48.595 --> 08:51.530
[panting]

08:51.532 --> 08:54.165
Hey, nice thinking, Twilight!

08:54.167 --> 08:56.768
Best-Aunt-Ever!

08:56.770 --> 08:59.304
Hang on, Flurry. The race
cart's taking a pit-stop.

09:08.981 --> 09:14.953
[giggling and happy shouts]

09:14.955 --> 09:16.054
[crash]

09:20.026 --> 09:22.994
I'm not a detective, but
I think we've got a suspect.

09:22.996 --> 09:24.129
Ah!

09:26.299 --> 09:27.699
[sigh]

09:27.701 --> 09:29.200
Well, we'd better
get to cleaning.

09:29.202 --> 09:30.702
We've got no
time to waste!

09:32.805 --> 09:35.073
Thanks, but they were
organized by color.

09:36.275 --> 09:37.576
[sigh]

09:47.587 --> 09:50.789
Yes! We gained back a whole
five minutes from running here!

09:50.791 --> 09:53.058
Yeah, but if you add
that to the 40 minutes

09:53.060 --> 09:57.128
we were already behind, we're
still... 55 minutes behind.

09:58.931 --> 10:01.099
I mean... yay, team?

10:01.101 --> 10:02.367
Mmhmm!

10:04.203 --> 10:07.038
Thanks for helping us out,
Cheerilee! Sorry we were late.

10:07.040 --> 10:08.940
Oh, no problem!

10:08.942 --> 10:10.976
But I gotta say, I'm
surprised you came to me

10:10.978 --> 10:14.379
for a book. Don't you
have a huge collection?

10:14.381 --> 10:18.783
Yes, but...
sorry, one second--

10:18.785 --> 10:21.987
[fussing]

10:23.789 --> 10:26.725
[happy shouts]

10:26.727 --> 10:28.360
I didn't think the
foals would be interested

10:28.362 --> 10:31.997
in The Unabridged History
of Amulets in Pony Latin.

10:31.999 --> 10:34.199
Yeah. It was good
you came to me.

10:34.201 --> 10:35.800
How about the
complete collection

10:35.802 --> 10:38.069
of "Ponyville
Fables and Stables"

10:40.139 --> 10:42.307
Mm, too long.

10:42.309 --> 10:44.976
"Alien Alicorns
vs. Space Pirates"?

10:44.978 --> 10:47.012
Well, the science
there is preposterous.

10:47.014 --> 10:49.314
How about Burnferno:
Warrior from Within?!

10:49.316 --> 10:51.983
It's about a handsome dragon
warrior who slays evildoers

10:51.985 --> 10:54.953
with his breath and
his snappy comebacks!

10:54.955 --> 10:59.424
Let's borrow that for you
and keep looking. What else?

10:59.426 --> 11:02.761
♪

11:10.436 --> 11:13.338
How about "Gusty
the Great"?

11:13.340 --> 11:15.440
Ooh! That was one
of my favorites

11:15.442 --> 11:18.376
when I was a filly!
We'll take it!

11:18.378 --> 11:21.946
Um... should I go with
something more current?

11:21.948 --> 11:23.314
[gasp]

11:23.316 --> 11:25.316
<i>♪ Ta da!</i>

11:25.318 --> 11:29.087
Cheerilee! I am so, so sorry.
I didn't even hear her leave.

11:38.397 --> 11:40.265
There! All clean!

11:40.267 --> 11:44.703
Great. Now I'll just write
it up again. With my mouth.

11:44.705 --> 11:45.904
[groan]

11:47.741 --> 11:52.444
This one's called 'A
Kitchen Guard's journey'.

11:52.446 --> 11:54.212
Oh...

11:54.214 --> 11:55.847
This reminds me
of the time

11:55.849 --> 11:58.216
Flurry got into the
chocolate pudding

11:58.218 --> 12:02.287
and we found little chocolate
hoofprints all over the carpet.

12:02.289 --> 12:04.456
That took forever
to clean up!

12:04.458 --> 12:06.391
But remember how cute
her little face looked

12:06.393 --> 12:08.026
when we caught her?

12:08.028 --> 12:10.962
Yeah she was
like... uh oh!

12:10.964 --> 12:12.764
[laughter]

12:12.766 --> 12:14.933
Whoa! Art is
so evocative.

12:14.935 --> 12:17.402
I wasn't even going
for that memory! Score!

12:20.306 --> 12:22.307
Honestly, Twilight, I
don't even want to tell you

12:22.309 --> 12:24.008
how late we are.

12:24.010 --> 12:25.944
Should I just cancel our
visit to the hospital?

12:25.946 --> 12:29.347
What? Cancel? We
can't cancel, Spike!

12:29.349 --> 12:31.483
The sick foals are
counting on us!

12:31.485 --> 12:34.853
And the B.A.E. would never
throw in the towel like that!

12:34.855 --> 12:36.321
B.A.E.?

12:36.323 --> 12:38.256
Best-Aunt-Ever!

12:38.258 --> 12:40.759
Besides, this errand is
going to be different!

12:40.761 --> 12:42.494
How do you figure that?

12:42.496 --> 12:44.796
Because Flurry can play
with the Cake twins

12:44.798 --> 12:47.198
and stay out of
trouble! Best Aunt Ever!

12:47.200 --> 12:53.371
♪

12:53.373 --> 12:57.242
[baby cooing]

12:57.244 --> 12:59.277
Wonderful, they're
friends already!

12:59.279 --> 13:01.012
Huh! I shouldn't
have doubted you.

13:01.014 --> 13:03.181
Thanks. Wait,
you doubted me?

13:04.550 --> 13:07.452
Spike, you watch Flurry; I'll
take care of everything else.

13:10.289 --> 13:12.924
Hi Pinkie, how's it going? I
need to pick up the cupcakes

13:12.926 --> 13:15.293
for the foals at the hospital
and can you do apology treats?

13:15.295 --> 13:18.196
I'm good. Here they
are. Of course I can!

13:18.198 --> 13:21.065
Do you still have a giant file
of everypony's favorite treat?

13:21.067 --> 13:22.834
In my secret party
planning cave.

13:22.836 --> 13:24.369
[ding]

13:24.371 --> 13:25.570
BRB!

13:28.574 --> 13:31.876
He he! Remind me to tell you
later how amazing you are.

13:31.878 --> 13:33.178
Cheerilee?

13:33.180 --> 13:34.479
I am pretty awesome.

13:37.283 --> 13:39.484
Cherry oatmeal cookies
with yellow sprinkles.

13:39.486 --> 13:41.953
Great! Can you write
"sorry" on them?

13:41.955 --> 13:43.454
I've got a stamp for that.

13:49.195 --> 13:51.329
[angry sounds]

13:59.338 --> 14:02.574
Hey, you guys.
no need to fight.

14:02.576 --> 14:04.576
Hang on! I'm sure
there's another one!

14:14.053 --> 14:16.120
Hold on, sweetie!
We'll play in a second!

14:30.169 --> 14:32.270
The salespony at
the toy store.

14:32.272 --> 14:34.505
Apple strudel cupcake
with caramel drizzle!

14:44.350 --> 14:47.318
Oh, no. You're making the
same face Cheerilee made.

14:47.320 --> 14:53.524
<i>♪ [horror movie stings]</i>

14:53.526 --> 14:57.128
Pinkie, remind me what
your favorite treat is.

14:57.130 --> 14:58.897
The sampler platter.

14:58.899 --> 15:00.265
We'll take
three of those.

15:02.301 --> 15:04.369
A-ha! told you I'd
find another one.

15:06.472 --> 15:07.605
Heh heh.

15:08.440 --> 15:10.008
[splat]

15:10.010 --> 15:12.010
♪

15:12.012 --> 15:13.945
Uh, Twilight!

15:13.947 --> 15:16.314
Out of the question! We
are NOT cancelling!

15:16.316 --> 15:18.316
It's going to be
OK! It has to be OK!

15:18.318 --> 15:21.319
that it can't possibly
end up [splat]

15:22.688 --> 15:25.023
Sorry.

15:25.025 --> 15:28.159
No, I needed it.

15:28.161 --> 15:30.128
I was just gonna
say... we're here.

15:33.532 --> 15:35.433
And we're only
four-and-a-half minutes late!

15:35.435 --> 15:38.036
Four-and-a-half?

15:38.038 --> 15:41.105
"And while nopony had ever
tried to reach Cloudsdale

15:41.107 --> 15:44.008
on hoof, Gusty the
Great was not deterred.

15:44.010 --> 15:46.711
She and her unicorn warriors
marched up the hill--

15:46.713 --> 15:49.213
but suddenly they encountered--"

15:49.215 --> 15:52.150
What?! What was it?!

15:52.152 --> 15:54.652
"It was the
treacherous Grogar!

15:54.654 --> 15:57.322
And Gusty could tell he
was ready for battle.

15:57.324 --> 15:59.624
Gusty called out to
the unicorn warriors--"

15:59.626 --> 16:01.459
OW!"

16:01.461 --> 16:04.729
Not right now, Flurry, these
foals really want to hear this.

16:04.731 --> 16:07.365
[crying]

16:07.367 --> 16:09.500
"'We can fight
Grogar... TOGETHER!'

16:09.502 --> 16:13.171
And the unicorn warriors shot
magical beams into the clouds

16:13.173 --> 16:15.039
that wove into one.

16:15.041 --> 16:18.409
The beam, stronger than a
thousand armies, shined down.

16:18.411 --> 16:21.446
It wrapped around Grogar and
pulled him to the ground.

16:21.448 --> 16:23.514
Don't let him escape!'
yelled Gusty!"--

16:23.516 --> 16:29.487
♪

16:29.489 --> 16:31.422
Say aaaaah!

16:31.424 --> 16:32.623
Aaah!

16:32.625 --> 16:35.760
♪

16:42.534 --> 16:46.004
"Grogar was strong,
for fear gave him power

16:46.006 --> 16:47.739
and he broke
through the bonds--"

16:47.741 --> 16:49.774
[whimpering]

16:49.776 --> 16:52.510
[alarmed sounds]

16:52.512 --> 16:54.345
I know! So good, right?!

16:54.347 --> 16:56.180
Spike: Twilight! Look up!

16:56.182 --> 16:58.349
Spike! You're floating!
YOU'RE FLOATING!

16:58.351 --> 16:59.617
So are you!

17:03.689 --> 17:06.090
Flurry, honey, you
need to stop this.

17:06.092 --> 17:07.692
Get us down, please!

17:07.694 --> 17:09.260
Twilight, look out!

17:10.496 --> 17:11.496
[gasp]

17:14.166 --> 17:15.266
[scream]

17:21.206 --> 17:23.775
Nopony panic! Everything's
going to be OK!

17:23.777 --> 17:27.111
♪

17:40.793 --> 17:43.261
Ah! I can't keep up with her!

17:43.263 --> 17:44.695
Oh, yeah! Where's her snoozal?

17:44.697 --> 17:48.499
You know her, whacky,
wompy-thing, the snail!

17:48.501 --> 17:50.601
Where is it? Cadance
said it calms her down!

17:50.603 --> 17:51.569
I don't see it!

17:51.571 --> 17:54.705
♪

18:01.747 --> 18:04.816
FLURRY HEART! PUT US
ALL DOWN THIS INSTANT!

18:07.753 --> 18:11.222
[screams]

18:11.224 --> 18:12.390
Is everypony OK?

18:16.228 --> 18:18.696
Flurry that was
very, very bad!

18:18.698 --> 18:20.231
You could have
hurt somepony.

18:20.233 --> 18:25.203
[bawling]

18:25.205 --> 18:28.139
Oh, Flurry, I didn't mean to--

18:28.141 --> 18:31.209
Sweetie, you don't have to be
scared; it's just me. See?

18:33.612 --> 18:36.814
Oh. You're scared of me.
Because I yelled at you.

18:36.816 --> 18:42.253
Flurry, I'm so sorry. I've
been a terrible aunt today.

18:42.255 --> 18:44.655
All you wanted to do was play

18:44.657 --> 18:47.391
and I've barely been able to
pay attention to you.

18:47.393 --> 18:50.361
None of this is your
fault. It's mine.

18:50.363 --> 18:53.164
So much for being
the Best Aunt Ever.

18:53.166 --> 18:56.501
But I hope you know
how much I love you.

18:56.503 --> 18:58.736
[giggle]

18:58.738 --> 19:01.305
I take it you forgive me?

19:01.307 --> 19:05.176
Thanks, Flurry. How
about we head home?

19:05.178 --> 19:07.311
After we find your
whammy, of course!

19:07.313 --> 19:08.813
Ahem!

19:12.351 --> 19:13.584
And clean up.

19:15.487 --> 19:18.489
This one kind of reminds
me of Flurry's hair.

19:20.826 --> 19:23.628
And this one reminds
me of Flurry, too.

19:23.630 --> 19:24.896
How so?

19:24.898 --> 19:28.299
It's small, like her.

19:28.301 --> 19:29.901
I can't do this
anymore.

19:29.903 --> 19:32.170
Spearhead, this has
been great but--

19:32.172 --> 19:33.704
Say no more.

19:33.706 --> 19:36.841
My art has always spoken
to me about what I love,

19:36.843 --> 19:39.644
but knowing that it spoke
to you about what you love,

19:39.646 --> 19:41.512
speaks to me.

19:41.514 --> 19:42.480
What?

19:42.482 --> 19:43.648
Go to her!

19:45.784 --> 19:47.618
[laughter]

19:47.620 --> 19:53.324
♪

19:53.326 --> 19:54.759
[baby giggle]

19:54.761 --> 19:57.895
♪

20:02.367 --> 20:04.535
Flurry? Where's our
little foal?

20:04.537 --> 20:07.939
♪

20:07.941 --> 20:10.308
We missed you so much!

20:16.381 --> 20:20.284
But it looks like you had
a great time without us.

20:20.286 --> 20:23.854
Actually, not so much. Flurry
got into some mischief.

20:23.856 --> 20:25.823
But it wasn't her fault.

20:25.825 --> 20:27.458
I shouldn't have
agreed to watch her

20:27.460 --> 20:29.594
with such a
jam-packed schedule.

20:29.596 --> 20:31.762
It was too much
to juggle.

20:31.764 --> 20:34.398
But Flurry taught me an
important lesson today.

20:34.400 --> 20:36.434
It turns out being the
Best Aunt Ever

20:36.436 --> 20:39.437
isn't about spending the
most time with your niece,

20:39.439 --> 20:41.906
but spending quality
time with her.

20:41.908 --> 20:44.842
And she taught me a
really cool "bear" game,

20:44.844 --> 20:46.644
so I guess I learned two things.

20:47.913 --> 20:49.981
[laughter]

20:49.983 --> 20:52.350
Well, we definitely
should have given you

20:52.352 --> 20:53.951
more of a head's up.

20:53.953 --> 20:57.788
Yes! From now on, we'll
give you plenty of notice.

20:57.790 --> 20:59.757
That would be great!

20:59.759 --> 21:01.359
Hey, what are you doing
next Tuesday?

21:02.427 --> 21:05.329
For dinner! Not to babysit.

21:05.331 --> 21:08.899
I'll have to check with Spike,
but I think we're free.

21:08.901 --> 21:11.369
Where is Spike, anyway?

21:11.371 --> 21:13.437
"... the dashing dragon warrior

21:13.439 --> 21:16.007
breathed a scorching
flame from his snout

21:16.009 --> 21:19.744
then chuckled to himself
as he flew into the sunset.

21:19.746 --> 21:23.281
'If you can't stand the heat,
don't fight a dragon..'"

21:23.283 --> 21:25.583
Hey, you kinda
look like him!

21:25.585 --> 21:27.351
Thank you.

21:27.353 --> 21:29.287
OK. Now who wants more cake?!

21:29.289 --> 21:31.355
[cheers]
